Isengard Axe x3<br>
The Palantír of Orthanc x2<br>
<br>
Servants to Saruman x2<br>
The Trees are Strong x1<br>
<br>
Trapped and Alone x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(36)">Spies of Saruman</a> x2<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> The idea of this deck started because I felt tired of playing always with Uruks, and also because of watching (almost) everybody playing with them. So I decided to change to another culture. With only one Morgul Gates, it was very difficult to design a powerfull Nazgûl deck, because choke is getting huge nowadays and Nazgûl can get very clogged against them. I have no problem on building a Moria deck, but wanted to played a smaller deck than it is normal for Moria. That brings me to Sauron or Isengard Orcs. Only one Orc Bowmen and one Enduring Evil destroys any chance of building a Wounding-Sauron deck or a Swarm-Sauron one, so I was left just with the new Isengard Orcs.<br>
For the Free Peoples I wanted to try something that may combine two really powerfull strategies: Superfellowship and Choke. Although it may look contradictory, I saw the European Championship deck, wich was trying something similar to it, and decided to try it.<br>
<br>
Free Peoples: Your normal starting company will be Sam and Legolas (Arwen if you expect Nazgûl). Bid high (5-6 depending on what you´re playing against) and take Aragorn out. If your opponent outbids you and don´t start the Pony, start Aragorn and topdeck for Sam. Once Aragorn is on the table, you will probably don´t give much twilight for playing your cards (almost every character cost 2 and weapons and conditions all cost 1; also Sting plays for free). Once Galadriel is in play, also your Elves will play for free. Characters (except Aragorn and Boromir) are all prescindable. Don´t be afraid of letting them die, as they are there just to do that (and also take wounds for you). Once Aragorn and Boromir are full-equiped, you will not have too many problems on winning skirmishes, specially with the archery help. This deck also does really well against Uruks, as both Armors and expendable characters make very difficult for them to destroy your fellowship. Although, watch for Saruman and never deploy a 5th companion unless you are sure (Sting) they have no Savagery on hand. Moria has nothing to do against this deck. 9 companions, archery and Secret Sentinels owns Moria. Against Sauron, again 9 companions, SS and also (and specially here) choke will destroy them. In addition, Pathfinder helps to deny them of Tol Brandir. Nazgûl could be something though at the begining, but once your main characters are boosted up, they have nothing to do.<br>
Probably this deck may not good in paper as good as it works on reallity, but keep in mind that it won the European Championship without losing any single game.<br>
<br>
Shadow: Isengard Orcs are a new culture, and due to that, is the weakest culture nowadays. Despite that, I think is not a bad a culture, and it´s also really funny to play with them. IsenOrcs CAN´T kill a company (or at least, is really difficult to them doing that), but when they make their job, they can make lots of wounds to your opponent, avoiding the double-move. Isengard Servants and Retainers are your main forces, while Commanders and Overseers are most like the elite ones. Overseer ability is really huge if you bring him alive till the regroup phase, exhausting the character you want. The main problems of IsenOrcs are weapons, archery and Superfellowship. To avoid the first one, you have Trapped and Alone, a must in every IsenOrc deck, that avoid the weapon´s damage bonus. For the second, Spies of Saruman and also Isengard Worker will help you escape of the archery. For me Superfellowships are not and IsenOrc problem, although I´ve heard that. If you feel like you can´t win a Superfellowship deck, change Gates of Argonath to Anduin Banks. That + Wastes may help a lot. Also may want to try Saruman´s Power, to combat Trust decks. If that´s huge on you area, substitute both Spies.<br>
<br>
Now for some chosen/no chosen cards:<br>
<br>
Sites 2, 4 and 7: They help my IsenOrcs to cause even more wounds.<br>
<br>
No Hollowing of Isengard/Tower of Orthanc: They don´t worth it. At the beginnig, you will alomst never have the pool to play an IsenOrc and a Hollowing, and on the later sites, 2 orcs is better than 1 and a Hollowin. Tower of Orthanc has a similar proble, because almost every deck nowadays have a healing sistem (Hobbit Hospital, Elrond HtGG, Galadriel LotGW, Aragorn KiE, etc...) that may heal that exhausted companion nulifying Tower purpose. In addition, I only own 1 Tower J.<br>
<br>
Saruman, SotE: Really HUGE here, he can make easier for your IsenOrcs to survive ´till regroup, and may also cause some extra wounds.<br>
<br>
Ulaire Enquea: Really usefull especially against those Superfellowship that (may) hurt IsenOrcs, and can help them on causing more wounds.<br>
<br>
No Tower Assasin: No Mirror made this Orc not as needed, although you may want to put one on your deck. In that case, substitute a Commander.<br>
<br>
No No Business of Ours: Same as above: no Mirror. Although, it may help against Sting you may want to add one or two, but I don´t feel them as if they were necesary.<br>
<br>
No Wizard Storm: It doesn´t work. It looks like it can, but really doesn´t do. Having 2 pool left after playing your orcs is no common, and prefer to save them for The Trees are Strong or the Palantir.<br>
<br>
Palantir of Orthanc: Really usefull against PATHS or SotSF to help your Orcs win their skirmishes. Really good here.<br>
<br>
Only 1 copy of each companion!!??: Well it was the first thing I thought wen I first see this deck, but it works. Your deck is almost a Plug and Play one, wich circles a lot and creates a big throughput that lets you get to your cards without much difficult. Also, you must discard a card each turn, to help the deck cicling. And don´t forget that most of your characters are prescindable, so don´t worry about them.<br>
<br>
The Trees are Strong: And increidble card that cand make your IsenOrcs living bombs. Use them till they´re exahusted and then sacrifice them to make even more wounds (only if fo feel like your opponent is not going to move again). Only one as I normally don´t need more.<br>
<br>
<br>
So, anyway, that´s the deck. Constructive criticism is allways apreciated. Thanks for reviewing and enjoy!!<br>
<br>
(Also sorry for my english, but i´m a Spanish player, and tried to write it as clear as I could to help you understand it.)<br>
<br>
(Current rating of this deck is 10-3 on causal play. Haven´t tried it on a tournament yet.)<br>
